# /privacy and /data-deletion are served automatically by Cloudflare
# Pages' auto-clean-URL behavior: privacy.html + data-deletion.html
# in this directory are reachable at /privacy and /data-deletion with
# no rule required. Adding 200-rewrite rules to the .html paths here
# creates an infinite loop against that auto-clean-URL redirect.
#
# /policy is registered as the privacy URL in the Google OAuth consent
# screen, but we want /privacy to be canonical. 301 the browser there.
/policy    /privacy    301

# SPA catch-all — everything else falls through to the React shell.
/*   /index.html   200
